problem: Find the coefficient of $x^2$ when $4(x - x^3) - 3(x^2 - x^3 + x^5) + 2(4x^2 - x^9)$ is simplified.
solution: The coefficient of $x^2$ in $4(x - x^3) - 3(x^2 - x^3 + x^5) + 2(4x^2 - x^9)$ is $-3 + 2 \cdot 4 = \boxed{5}$.

$4(x - x^3) - 3(x^2 - x^3 + x^5) + 2(4x^2 - x^9) = 4x - 4x^3 - 3x^2 + 3x^3 - 3x^5 + 8x^2 - 2x^9$
Combine like terms.

$4x - 4x^3 - 3x^2 + 3x^3 - 3x^5 + 8x^2 - 2x^9 = 4x - 4x^3 - 3x^2 + 3x^3 - 3x^5 + 8x^2 - 2x^9$
Combine like terms.

$4x - 4x^3 - 3x^2 + 3x^3 - 3x^5 + 8x^2 - 2x^9 = 4x + x^3 - 5x^2 - 3x^5 - 2x^9$
There is no additional step, the previous step is the final step.
